				<div class="postbody">
				We really do not want 10 to 12 major political parties.  Look at Italy for an example on how that is working out for them.  Nearly all of the major powerful countries in the world have primarly two parties; from Japan to the UK to the US and Canada, etc.
<br />

<br />
My views for the most part are Libertarian and heck I think most people actually do fall into the libertarian category but just do not know this.
<br />
However, I am also realistic and know that we are a two party system, therefore in most cases I vote Republican.
<br />
The last election, though, I did vote libertarian to do my part in helping them get their 5%, or whatever it is they were required to get for federal campaign funding.
<br />

<br />
I just can not bring myself to vote Democrat, they seem to be so of touch with reality and have no opinion what so ever.  Their party platform seems to be "We don't know what we believe in, except whatever Bush and Co. is doing is wrong and we believe in the opposite of whatever they are doing."<br />
